### Hadith 4:380

*Narrated Ibn 'Umar:*

Umar bin Al-Khattab expelled all the Jews and Christians from the land
of Hijaz. Allah's Apostle after conquering Khaibar, thought of expelling
the Jews from the land which, after he conquered it belonged to Allah,
Allah's Apostle and the Muslims. But the Jews requested Allah's Apostle
to leave them there on the condition that they would do the labor and
get half of the fruits (the land would yield). Allah's Apostle said, "We
shall keep you on these terms as long as we wish." Thus they stayed till
the time of 'Umar's Caliphate when he expelled them to Taima and Ariha.

